gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 132, Spurs 119
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Spurs, 132-119. Damian Lillard led the way with 40 points and seven 3PM for the Bucks, while Bobby Portis (23 points, 10 rebounds) and Giannis Antetokounmpo (11 points, 14 rebounds, career-high 16 assists) combined for 34 points in the victory. Keldon Johnson tallied 28 points and 12 rebounds for the Spurs in the losing effort. The Bucks have won their 5th consecutive game and improve to 20-7 on the season, while the Spurs fall to 4-22.
